Macron's slow shift toward recognizing the State of Palestine
byline: By Claire Gatinois and Philippe Ricard
subhed: After expressing unwavering support for Israel, the French president gradually shifted his stance on the two-state solution following October 7, 2023, and the conflict in Gaza. This reversal will culminate in France's official recognition of the State of Palestine at the UN on September 22.

Trump and members of the MAGA movement pay tribute at Charlie Kirk's memorial
subhed: The memorial service for Kirk, whom Trump credits with playing a pivotal role in his 2024 election victory, drew tens of thousands of mourners. Security was tight, and speakers delivered their tributes behind bullet-proof glass.

title: 'Immigration must be treated as an economic and social issue, not a moral one'
subhed: Immigration is a volatile issue in the US, the UK and France. Claiming − as some on the French left do − that the issue's magnitude is the result of political manipulation reveals a form of blindness, argues Le Monde columnist Philippe Bernard.

title: The antique map collection is a market waiting to be rediscovered
subhed: A rare collection of engravings by cosmographer André Thevet, including several particularly unusual sheets, is set to be auctioned in Paris on September 24. The starting price is set at €10,000, but the auction house is hoping for a bidding frenzy.

title: Giverny's thriving business around Monet's gardens risks oversaturation
subhed: Chinese and American film shoots and a prime minister who has made it his home base: Just an hour from Paris, this village of 460 residents draws hundreds of thousands of visitors. Yet its fame brings little benefit to the locals.

title: 'Are there words left to describe the horror we are wreaking on Gaza?'
subhed: Noam Ben-Zeev and Yael Perlov, two prominent figures from Israel's cultural scene, express their deep attachment to Palestine and its people. Now exiled in France, they call on European countries to mobilize to save Gaza – and, by doing so, Israel itself.

title: France's situation causes concern in Brussels
subhed: The country's political instability, the rise of the far right and deteriorating public finances are worrying its European partners. The appointment of PM Sébastien Lecornu, who has so far not been very involved in EU affairs, has done little to reassure them.
